Two cable thieves were electrocuted while attempting to steal copper cabling from an Eskom transformer near Glencoe in northern KwaZulu-Natal this week.Their bodies were found near a transformer by Eskom workers after a power outage.Sanele Madlala and Bongani Khubeka both of Sithembile were wearing protective gloves but the current appears to have passed through them while they were attempting to pull the cables.The rain may have exacerbated the situation, an Eskom official said.Police spokesperson Veli Mbhense said copper wire theft was on the increase in the area.Langelihle Chagwe | provinces@thenewage.co.za